WARRI – The leadership of Host Communities of Nigeria, Producing Oil and Gas HOSTCOM Urhobo Ethnic Nationality Youth Wing has Congratulated Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori, the Speaker of Delta State House of Assembly for winning the PDP primaries on Thursday. The congratulatory message was contained in a message signed by Comrade Sweet Otiotiothe Leader of the HOSTCOM Youth Wing Urhobo Ethnic Nationality and Comrade Happy Gbeke as Secretary stated that the resounding victory of Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori is an attestation to his acceptability across the board as a detribalised leader. Comrade Sweet Otiotio noted in his statement that the selfless services of SheriffOborevwori has been rendering for Deltans through effective party Participation in the democratic processing is what motivated the party leadership in Delta State to trust him with the exalted position of Governorship candidate. -Advertisement- According to Comrade Sweet Otiotio, the Urhobo HOSTCOM Youth Wing boss,based on the excellent performance of Sheriff Oborevwori as the Speaker of the State House of Assembly, we have no iota of doubt that he will take Delta State to greater heights if elected Governnor come 2023. Speaking further, he added: “Now that the primaries have come and gone, we enjoin all those who contested with Sheriff Oborevwori to rally around himin the democratic spirit of one big family to garner victory for the PDP during the general elections. Comrade Happy Gbeke, the Secretary of HOSTCOM Urhobo Youth Wing who also spokein his congratulatory message posited that the transparent, free and credible manner the PDP primaries were conducted shows that RT. Hon Sheriff Oborevwori truly deserves the victory, as the verdict reflected the true choice of the people. Comrade Happy Gbeke, the Urhobo HOSTCOM Youth scribe observed in his goodwill message to Sheriff Oborevwori that HOSTCOM Youths believes that with him in the saddle of leadership, there will be enough dividends of democracy for all in his incoming administration. He called on Youths across the board, the women and all relevant stakeholders tomobilise as usual for the success of Oborevwori, during the general election because Delta is for PDP the Way PDP is for Delta, he concluded.